/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-091e84d elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"091e84d\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-7024b60\" data-id=\"7024b60\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-63a9283 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"63a9283\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Diagnosis<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Sx: <strong>Gross Hematuria<\/strong> (Very Reliable, 95-100%), Pain &amp; Low Urine Output<\/li><li>Dx: <strong>CT Cystography<\/strong> (Inject \u2265 300 cc Contrast Through Foley)<ul><li><em>Intraperitoneal Leak<\/em>: Outlines Loops of Bowel or Fills Cul-De-Sac<\/li><li><em>Extraperitoneal Leak<\/em>: <strong>Flame or Starbursts<\/strong><\/li><li>If Conventional Cystography (XR Fluoroscopy) Must Obtain Post-Drainage Films<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Treatment<\/strong><\/p><ul><li><em>Extraperitoneal Rupture<\/em>:<ul><li>Uncomplicated: <strong>Foley<\/strong> (7-14 Weeks)<\/li><li>Complicated: Surgical Repair<ul><li>Indications:<ul><li>Open Pelvic Fracture with Bone Exposed in Bladder Lumen<\/li><li>Concurrent Vaginal\/Rectal Injury (Risk for Fistula)<\/li><li>Bladder Neck Injury<\/li><li>Persistent Hematuria\/Clots (Will Obstruct Foley)<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Intraperitoneal Rupture<\/em>:<strong> Surgical Repair<\/strong> &amp; Foley<ul><li>Use <strong>Absorbable<\/strong> Sutures in <strong>2 Layers<\/strong> (Permanent Irritate Mucosa &amp; Are Lithogenic)<\/li><li>Cystogram Every 7-10 Days to Evaluate for Foley Removal<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-04d2f22\" data-id=\"04d2f22\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ad215d9 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"ad215d9\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-11844 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Bladder-Cysto-Intraperitoneal.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"606\" srcset=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Bladder-Cysto-Intraperitoneal.jpg 500w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/05\/Bladder-Cysto-Intraperitoneal-248x300.jpg 248w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/p><p>Intraperitoneal Bladder Injury <sup>2<\/sup><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-elemen